In the 1480s [[DR]],{{ToD-time}} the [[Cult of the Dragon]] began searching for the five ''Dragon Masks'' across the Realms. Their search spanned the breadth of [[Faer√ªn]], from an expedition in [[Frozenfar]] led by their [[Red Wizard]] ally [[Rath Modar]],{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 1}} to another in the [[Moonsea]] led by the "cult traditionalist" [[wizard]] named [[Ixas]].{{Cite adventurers league/Shadows over the Moonsea|5}} 

The cult's leader [[Severin Silrajin]] recovered the ''[[Red Dragon Mask]]'' himself of the isle of [[Tuern]],{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 5}} while the ''[[White Dragon Mask]]'' was recovered, and subsequently lost to a devious [[Zhentarim]] [[Ratshadow|agent]] a short time later.{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 6}} 

The ''[[Green Dragon Mask|Green]]'' and ''[[Black Dragon Mask]]s'' and were found and stashed away at the [[Misty Forest]] and [[Skyreach Castle]] respectively. The former was secreted away to the cult's citadel at the [[Well of Dragons]] for use in their dark ritual, while the fate of the latter remained unknown for a time.

Eventually, all five of the masks were brought to the Well of Dragon, and Severin Silrajin assembled the complete ''Mask of the Dragon Queen''.{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 8}} Unfortunately the cult's actions attracted the attention of the most powerful factions of the [[Sword Coast]].{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 9}} Severin completed his ritual to summon his goddess [[Tiamat]] to the Realms, but the cult's success was brief. Tiamat was defeated and cast back down to the [[Nine Hells]], Severin was apprehended for his crimes, and the cult's forces were scattered.{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 10}}
